President Donald J. Trump issued a Presidential Memorandum on September 25, 2017, delegating authority to the Secretary of State under the Consolidated Appropriations Act, 2017. This memorandum grants the Secretary of State the functions and authorities vested in the President by section 10006 of the Act. The delegation stated in the memorandum will also apply to any provision of any future public law that is the same or substantially the same as section 10006 of the Act. The memorandum directs the Secretary of State to publish it in the Federal Register.